<br>
Sure, wizards out nuke us 2 to 1 but Wizards NEED mana to do damage and a manaless Wizard is as good as a dead duck. While we are out of mana, we're still doing damage through our pets which can many times turn the tide from a possible wipeout to a victory.<br>
<br>
About the mod rod nerf I think I would rather be in the heat of battle battling along side Jabober rather than sit on my ass and become a walking mod rod dispensing machine (read: mod rod whore).<br>
<br>
Take a good look at the PoP spells: We get to summon some nifty stuff that NO OTHER CLASSES can. We will be in demand for our focus items. Soon, we will be in demand for our gate rings as well as proccing weapons (stun/dd proc). You can either give them away for free or make money out of it. Personally, I won't mind too if Verant would give us something that procs slow on mobs (that would make us even better soloers). <br>
<br>
As for the deal with the Dire Charm: Dire charm is limited to level 46 mobs. You can't always find a mob that you can Dire charm but we can always find our faithful Jabober or Jabaner at our side ready to do battle.<br>
